x4freetext: IEA-R1 2 MV pool type research reactor.
The irradiations have been performed near the
reactor core, very close to the fuel element.
The neutron spectrum at the irradiation position has
been characterized by multiple foil activation techni-
que in combination with computer codes for data ana-
lysis, and has been found to be similar to an U-235
fission spectrum.
Metal foils or wires of natural isotopic composition
and with purity by weight higher than 99.9%
( reactor experiments inc., USA)
All samples were counted in a well defined
geometry (172 mm from the detector).
